OBJECTIVE
  Understanding how modifying query parameters can impact backend authorization logic.
 LAB ENVIRONMENT
  Browser:firefox
    Proxy Tool:Burp suite
      Test Endpoint: httpbin.org
        WHAT I DID
        intercepted a GET request containing a query parameter.
        Modified name=emunah to another value
        Added hidden parameters such as role=admin.
        Observed how the server reflected user-supplied input.
        KEY OBSERVATION
        the backend accepted additional parameters even when tey were not originally present in the request.
        Example modified request:
        GET/get?user=emunah&role=adminHTTP/1.1
        SECURITY INSIGHT
        if a real application blindly trusts user-controlled parameters such as role,this could lead to privilege escalation
        frontend validation is not security.Authorization must be enforced server-side.
        CONCEPT LEARNED
        Parameter Tampering can expose broken access control vulnerabilities.
